  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know when you are going into the friendzone?",
  "response": "Recognizing the signs of entering the friendzone can help you understand the dynamics of your relationship and manage your expectations. Here are some common indicators that you might be heading into the friendzone:\n\n1. **Lack of Flirtation**: If your interactions lack flirtation or romantic undertones, and feel more like casual, friendly conversations, it could be a sign.\n\n2. **They Talk About Other Romantic Interests**: If they frequently discuss their crushes, dates, or romantic interests with you, it might indicate they see you more as a friend.\n\n3. **Physical Boundaries**: If they maintain physical distance and avoid intimate contact like hugs, holding hands, or cuddling, it could be a sign that they don\u2019t see you in a romantic way.\n\n4. **They Seek Your Advice on Dating**: If they ask for your advice on how to pursue someone else romantically, it\u2019s a clear indication they value your friendship but don\u2019t see you as a potential partner.\n\n5. **Group Hangouts**: If you mostly hang out in group settings and rarely have one-on-one time that feels like a date, it might suggest a platonic relationship.\n\n6. **No Jealousy**: If they show no signs of jealousy or concern when you talk about other people you\u2019re interested in, it could mean they see you as just a friend.\n\n7. **Labeling You as a Friend**: If they introduce you to others as their \u201cfriend\u201d or use phrases like \u201che/she is like a brother/sister to me,\u201d it\u2019s a clear sign of the friendzone.\n\n8. **Comfort Level**: If they are overly comfortable with you to the point where they feel free to be their absolute, unfiltered self without worrying about impressing you, it might indicate a platonic relationship.\n\n9. **Communication Style**: If their texts or calls are sporadic and don\u2019t have a flirty or intimate tone, it could suggest they\u2019re not interested romantically.\n\n10. **You Feel It**: Often, your intuition can tell you if someone sees you as more than a friend. If you feel like you\u2019re being treated differently than their other romantic interests, trust your gut.\n\nUnderstanding these signs can help you navigate your feelings and decide how to move forward, whether that means expressing your feelings, accepting the friendship, or taking some space.",
